OL,3,CCalls for more understanding of
OL,4,Cepilepsy as report shows health board
OL,5,Cfailings
OL,7,F"Not just this, Wales has a higher
OL,8,Frate of incidence of epilepsy than the
OL,9,Frest of the UK and the epilepsy
OL,10,Fpopulation is growing, but services
OL,11,Fcontinue to be underfunded and, very
OL,12,Fobviously, not meeting the standards.
OL,13,FThis needs to change. Now."
OL,15,FA Welsh Government spokesperson said:
OL,16,F"We have set out what we expect of
OL,17,Fhealth boards to ensure people living
OL,18,Fwith or affected by a neurological
OL,19,Fcondition, including epilepsy, have
OL,20,Ftimely and equitable access to high-
OL,21,Fquality services.
